{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"61904ebc-e33f-4601-8aad-7218eb192e57","content":"Your `.testsettings` file configures three things: assembly resolution/deployment, a 30-second test timeout, and a code coverage collector. **MSTest v3 dropped `.testsettings` support** — you need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nHere's the migration:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_P71d80UB1z3gvpqMkdeDxq","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Migrating testsettings to runsettings"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"tooluse_kUKbeAYqu5NxBoBSkHuM0C","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5db0b2ab09084e8492ebf16a0158f222/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Replaces AssemblyResolution/TestDirectory useLoadContext=\"true\" -->\n    <DeploymentEnabled>false</DeploymentEnabled>\n    <!-- Replaces TestSettings Property TestTimeout (in milliseconds) -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <!-- Replaces AgentRule CodeCoverage DataCollector -->\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=b03f5f7f11d50a3a\" />\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-5db0b2ab09084e8492ebf16a0158f222/local.runsettings."}],"interactionId":"5397372b-4caf-4b1c-a6a8-29772c2b92fc","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file with:\n1. Assembly resolution / test deployment config\n2. A test timeout of 30000ms (30 seconds)\n3. A code coverage data collector\n\nIn MSTest v3, `.testsettings` files are no longer supported. The user needs to migrate to a `.runsettings` file and MSTest v3 attributes/configuration.\n\nLet me explain how to migrate each piece:\n\n1. **Test timeout**: In MSTest v3, you can set a default timeout via `.runsettings` under the `<MSTest>` section using `<TestTimeout>`, or via `[Timeout]` attribute on individual tests.\n\n\n2. **Code coverage data collector**: This goes into a `.runsettings` file under `<DataCollectors>`.\n3. **Assembly resolution / deployment**: MSTest v3 handles deployment differently. The `<DeploymentEnabled>` setting can be set in `.runsettings` under `<MSTest>`.\n\nNow I'll create a `.runsettings` file that replaces the `.testsettings` configuration and update the `.csproj` to reference it.","outputTokens":745,"requestId":"63C2:38FB84:3D25CD3:434CBD5:6A02FA4B"},"id":"b9e16459-48ab-40ce-a60f-c8236f6ee004","timestamp":"2026-05-12T10:00:56.666Z","parentId":"7680d8d0-6030-4776-99a1-8da05d597a3f"}
